        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "MOOC",
          "Next Question is Correct on First Attempt ",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "2000 EdX learners",
          "Course 6.002X: Circuit Design",
          "LMS logs, ",
          "[Activities associated with a specific problem]",
          "In intelligent tutoring systems there is a connection of the Knowledge Components associated with each Question in the System.\n\nGetting experts to map questions to knowledge components is not trivial in a MOOC context. Moreover, in a MOOC setting, KC are often treated in isolation, leaving little chance to see evolution of KCs over time.\n\nMOOCs also have a different form of accepting an answer as correct and /or incorrect - ITS use first answer, MOOC often consider last attempt.\n",
          "The authors’ implementation of BKT includes a variant that allows the observation of multiple subparts at once (IDEM). \n\nIt also includes a parameter to measure the number of attempts needed to get the correct answer (Count). ",
          "Logs were separated by user and the representation of each user is the sequence of activities associated with a problem. ",
          "BKT,\nBKT-count, \nBKT-IDEM, \nBKT-IDEM-Count",
          "5-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "Exam:\n{AUC: 0,6575 - BKT-IDEM-Count}\n\nLEC:\n{AUC: 0,596 - BKT-IDEM-Count}\n\nHW:\n{AUC: 0.6814 - BKT-IDEM-Count}",
          "Fitting of BKT model was done via Expectation-Maximization. \n\nModels are divided into types of materials. Authors analyze the results in terms of problem types: Homework problems, Lccture Problems and finally Exam Problems.\n\nThe model is percurssor for KT in MOOCs with 2 that address 2 challenges:\n\n1. Lack of a KC model for MOOCs,\n\n2. Unpenalized Attempts Counts \n",
          "Authors only publish results using AUC score.\n\nComparison with ASSISTments scores is soewhat unnecessary as interpretation of contexts is substantially different.\n\nSubpart separation is not ideal to predict success throughut the course.\n\nA single dataset and course.\n\nNo extension to DKT framework, focusing only in BKT."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 3
    }
  ],
